In April 2021 (just last month), Dogecoin and other cryptocurrencies surged, stimulated in part by the direct listing for cryptocurrency exchange Coinbase

Dogecoin's price first reached $0.10 on April 14, before hitting a new high of $0.45 on April 16 🚀

In March 2021, Dallas Mavericks owner Mark Cuban announced his NBA team would allow purchasing tickets and products with Dogecoin

Within two days, Cuban had declared his franchise had become the top Dogecoin merchant, having carried out 20,000 transactions https://t.co/OcWWijH9uU
In January 2021, Dogecoin went up over 800% in 24 hours, attaining a price of $0.07, as a result of attention from Reddit users (and some guy who goes by @elonmusk) https://t.co/UDcIE3zsIg

During the 2017 to early 2018 cryptocurrency bubble, Dogecoin briefly reached a peak of $0.017/coin 

(Little over 1 cent? Are you kidding me?)

In July 2020, the price of Dogecoin spiked following a TikTok trend aiming to get the coin's price to $1 https://t.co/wAQgcEw93P

Dogecoin started its initial coin production schedule with 100 billion coins in circulation

By mid-2015 the 100 billionth Dogecoin had been mined with an additional 5 billion coins put into circulation every year thereafter https://t.co/G4asbKYQsq

In Jan 2014, the trading volume of Dogecoin briefly surpassed that of Bitcoin and all other cryptocurrencies combined 😮

Initially, Dogecoin featured a randomized reward for each mining block, however, in March 2014 this behavior was updated to a static block (consistent) reward

To help those who lost funds on Dogewallet after its breach, the Dogecoin community started an initiative named "SaveDogemas" to help donate coins to those who had them stolen 

Approximately one month later, enough money was donated to cover all of the coins that were stolen https://t.co/SQTdgI2UrF

On December 25, 2013, the first major theft of Dogecoin occurred when millions of coins were stolen during a hack of the online cryptocurrency wallet platform Dogewallet

The hacker modified the platform's send/receive page to send all coins to the hacker's address

Markus designed Dogecoin's protocol based on existing cryptocurrencies Luckycoin and Litecoin

On December 19, 2013, Dogecoin jumped nearly 300 percent in value in 72 hours, rising from US$0.00026 to $0.00095 

(imagine selling at that price...) https://t.co/zuSUTnOwTS

Palmer purchased the domain Dogecoin(.com) and added the logo and some text - Markus reached out after seeing the site; together they coded Dogecoin

Officially launching on December 6, 2013, there were over a million visitors to Dogecoin's site within the first 30 days  😅

Dogecoin was created by IBM software engineer Billy Markus and Adobe software engineer Jackson Palmer, who set out to create a peer-to-peer digital currency that could reach a broader demographic than Bitcoin https://t.co/q1ryOt0fxW

In 2021 alone, Dogecoin is up 6,000% 🚀

If you invested $1000 on Jan 1, 2021, you'd be holding $60,000 - in just four months...
